  <md:title>Heterodont animals</md:title>
  <md:abstract>Mammals evolved a heterodont dentition with four classes of teeth: incisors, canines, premolars and molars. Each tooth is formed by 1-5 cusps. Maxillary cusps are called cones whereas mandibular ones are called conids. Hypsodont teeth erupt high beyond the gum line while brachydont teeth do not protrude much. The shape and arrangement of tissues in the molar teeth is grouped into several classes that reflect the diet and phylogeny of the animals.</md:abstract>
